element.name: HQ (Luxembourg)
element.documentation: houses top management, as well as finance, quality management, product development, and human resources (HR) departments

element.name: Production Center
element.documentation: procures raw materials and uses them to manufacture products, which it stores in warehouses and distributes to DCs.

element.name: DC Benelux (Belgium)
element.documentation: Serve the company's construction sector customers

element.name: DC Spain
element.documentation: Serve the company's construction sector customers

element.name: Finance
element.documentation: defines policies and procedures and rules that the DCs must follow when they set prices and assess the credit risk associated with individual customers.

element.name: Production
element.documentation: The PC Production function plans, executes, and monitors manufacturing, and also plans, designs, constructs, and maintains manufacturing facilities.

element.name: Procurement
element.documentation: The PC Procurement function selects suppliers and negotiates contracts with them. The function also forecasts demand for raw materials, orders, them, and manages inventory levels, relying heavily on information form the Sales and Production functions.

element.name: Logistics
element.documentation: The Logistics function transports and stores both raw materials and finished goods.

element.name: Sales
element.documentation: The PC Sales function forecasts sales, takes consolidated orders from DCs, and shares them with the Manufacturing and Logistics functions.

element.name: Distribution
element.documentation: in charge of transporting the finished goods to the customer

element.name: Customer Relations
element.documentation: The Customer Relations function in each DC assesses credit risk, works with sales representatives to negotiate contracts, leads responses to customer compliants, ensures collection of accounts payable, and manages customer master data. The sales function is responsible for sales activities, including handling customer orders from their registration in the system until the invoicing, which is the responsibility of the Finance function
